cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use magentabook, please cite it as below."
title: "magentabook: HM Treasury Magenta Book Policy Evaluation Primitives"
authors:
  - family-names: Coverdale
    given-names: Charles
    email: charlesfcoverdale@gmail.com
type: software
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-04-27
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/charlescoverdale/magentabook"
url: "https://github.com/charlescoverdale/magentabook"
abstract: >-
  Implements policy-evaluation primitives from HM Treasury Magenta Book
  guidance: theory of change and logframe construction, evaluation
  planning and stakeholder mapping, power and minimum-detectable-effect
  calculations including cluster and stepped-wedge designs, Maryland
  Scientific Methods Scale ratings, structured confidence ratings,
  light-weight difference-in-differences and interrupted-time-series
  estimators, and cost-effectiveness analysis (cost per outcome,
  incremental cost-effectiveness ratio, acceptability curves,
  incremental net benefit, quality-adjusted and disability-adjusted
  life years). Designed as the evaluation companion to the appraisal
  package greenbook.
keywords:
  - r
  - economics
  - evaluation
  - policy
  - magenta book
  - cost-effectiveness
  - power-analysis
  - hm-treasury
